comment:
* Represents the codec status (configuration and capability) for a Bluetooth Le Audio source
 * device.
 *
 * @see BluetoothLeAudio

variables.name: EXTRA_LE_AUDIO_CODEC_STATUS
variables.comment:
* Extra for the codec configuration intents of the individual profiles. * *

This extra represents the current codec status of the Le Audio profile.

methods.name: private static boolean sameCapabilities(@Nullable List<BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig> c1, @Nullable List<BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig> c2)
methods.comment:
* Checks whether two lists of capabilities contain same capabilities. The order of the
     * capabilities in each list is ignored.
     *
     * @param c1 the first list of capabilities to compare
     * @param c2 the second list of capabilities to compare
     * @return {@code true} if both lists contain same capabilities

methods.name: public boolean isInputCodecConfigSelectable(@Nullable BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig codecConfig)
methods.comment:
* Checks whether the Input codec config matches the selectable capabilities. Any parameters of
     * the codec config with NONE value will be considered a wildcard matching.
     *
     * @param codecConfig the codec config to compare against
     * @return {@code true} if the codec config matches, {@code false} otherwise

methods.name: public boolean isOutputCodecConfigSelectable(@Nullable BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig codecConfig)
methods.comment:
* Checks whether the Output codec config matches the selectable capabilities. Any parameters of
     * the codec config with NONE value will be considered a wildcard matching.
     *
     * @param codecConfig the codec config to compare against
     * @return {@code true} if the codec config matches, {@code false} otherwise

methods.name: public int hashCode()
methods.comment: Returns a hash based on the codec config and local capabilities.

methods.name: public String toString()
methods.comment:
* Returns a {@link String} that describes each BluetoothLeAudioCodecStatus parameter current
     * value.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
methods.comment:
* Flattens the object to a parcel.
     *
     * @param out The Parcel in which the object should be written
     * @param flags Additional flags about how the object should be written

methods.name: public BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig getInputCodecConfig()
methods.comment:
* Returns the current Input codec configuration.
     *
     * @return The current input codec config.

methods.name: public BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig getOutputCodecConfig()
methods.comment:
* Returns the current Output codec configuration.
     *
     * @return The current output codec config.

methods.name: public List<BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig> getInputCodecLocalCapabilities()
methods.comment:
* Returns the input codecs local capabilities.
     *
     * @return The list of codec config that supported by the local system.

methods.name: public List<BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig> getOutputCodecLocalCapabilities()
methods.comment:
* Returns the output codecs local capabilities.
     *
     * @return The list of codec config that supported by the local system.

methods.name: public List<BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig> getInputCodecSelectableCapabilities()
methods.comment:
* Returns the Input codecs selectable capabilities.
     *
     * @return The list of codec config that supported by both of the local system and remote
     *     devices.

methods.name: public List<BluetoothLeAudioCodecConfig> getOutputCodecSelectableCapabilities()
methods.comment:
* Returns the Output codecs selectable capabilities.
     *
     * @return The list of codec config that supported by both of the local system and remote
     *     devices.
